Name: liboqs (Open Quantum Safe)
Short Name: liboqs
URL: https://github.com/open-quantum-safe/liboqs
Version: 0.10.0
License: MIT
License File: src/LICENSE.txt
Security Critical: yes
Shipped: yes

Description:
liboqs is an open-source C library for quantum-safe cryptographic algorithms.
It provides implementations of post-quantum key encapsulation mechanisms (KEMs)
and digital signature algorithms as standardized by NIST:
  - ML-KEM (FIPS 203, formerly CRYSTALS-Kyber) — key encapsulation
  - ML-DSA (FIPS 204, formerly CRYSTALS-Dilithium) — digital signatures

ArjunBrowser uses liboqs for:
  - ML-KEM-768 hybrid key exchange (X25519 + ML-KEM-768) in TLS 1.3
  - ML-DSA-65 server certificate signature verification
  - NIST Known-Answer Test (KAT) validation

Local Modifications:
  - BUILD.gn created for Chromium GN build system integration
  - Source files compiled with Chromium-compatible warning suppressions
  - Configured to enable only ML-KEM-{512,768,1024} and ML-DSA-{44,65,87}
